718978f-a.title: Manhattan: Claremont Avenue - 116th Street (West)
718978f-a.text:
Claremont Avenue, west side (buildings there upon), from
W.116th Street and Riverside Driwe (left) to a point on a line
with W. 118th Sitreet, showing apartment structures formerly
occupied by Barnard College students and that now house the
faculty. TThey are, from left to right, the Paterno, the dual
Barnard Court, the Sophomore, the 11 story Peter Minuit and
Etoon Hall. The photographer is viewirg westward from Sroadway
ard across the fenced 1ot where the present (in 1938) Barnard
College Students Building stards.
October 1914.
